<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> Quoted by Stinnett (note 8 to Chapter 2), Whitlock expressly contradicts Stinnett's thesis.</li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qa3926/is_200307/ai_n9291658/pg_3" class="external text" title="http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qa3926/is_200307/ai_n9291658/pg_3" rel="nofollow">Foreknowledge of Pearl Harbor? No!: The story of the U. S. Navy's efforts on JN-25B | Cryptologia | Find Articles at BNET</a> at www.findarticles.com</li>
